<subSubSection id="F5B8A4FFDE47FFBAFC92FA0EFB5DF7F0" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BD1DF774DE47FFBAFC92FA0EFB5DF7F0" blockId="1.[794,1400,1417,2081]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
Diagnosis (based on males). Large-sized species of 
<taxonomicName id="7AA28CF7DE47FFBAFAB2FA0EFCCBFA10" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FD62B66DE47FFBAFAB2FA0EFCCBFA10" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Chrysotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="7A5A5A91DE47FFBAFCECFA2EFC26FA10" box="[868,931,1449,1473]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
or longer). Face and frons with parallel sides. Antennae yellow to orange, postpedicel sometimes brownish; antennal stylus apical. Thorax mostly shinning green, eventually with yellow areas (e.g., metepimere); acrostichals absent; six pairs of dorsocentrals; upper part of proepisternum, in front of anterior spiracle, bare. Wing: membrane hyaline or smoked, sometimes with a conspicuous transversal brown stripe; veins R 
<subScript id="2126F531DE47FFBAFB1EF91EFB2BF976" attach="left" box="[1174,1198,1689,1703]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">4+5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript id="2126F531DE47FFBAFB7FF91EFB7BF976" attach="left" box="[1271,1278,1689,1703]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">1</subScript>
subparallel and slightly moved posteriad; distal section of vein CuA shorter than crossvein dm-cu (see 
<bibRefCitation id="D9338A85DE47FFBAFB1AF94EFAA1F930" author="BECKER, T." box="[1170,1316,1737,1761]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="1 - 394" refId="ref5517" refString="BECKER, T. 1922: Dipterologische Studien. Dolichopodidae. B. Nearktische und neotropische Region. - Abhandlungen der zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 13 (1): 1 - 394, 147 figs." type="book chapter" year="1922">BECKER 1922</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 63; 
<bibRefCitation id="D9338A85DE47FFBAFC92F96EFC28F8D0" author="PARENT, O." box="[794,941,1769,1793]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="169 - 246" refId="ref5913" refString="PARENT, O. 1929: Etude sur les Dolichopodides exotiques de la Collection von Roder. - Annales de la Societe scientifique de Bruxelles (B) 49: 169 - 246, 124 figs." type="book chapter" year="1929">PARENT 1929</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 30, 1931: fig. 24, 1934: pl. 68, fig. 14; 
<bibRefCitation id="D9338A85DE47FFBAFC92F88EFBCDF8F0" author="CAPELLARI, R. S. &amp; AMORIM, D. S." box="[794,1096,1801,1825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="49 - 65" refId="ref5599" refString="CAPELLARI, R. S. &amp; AMORIM, D. S. 2010: Re-description and new combination of five New World species of Chrysotus MEIGEN, with comments on the Neotropical genus Lyroneurus LOEW (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). - Zootaxa 2520: 49 - 65, 25 figs." type="book chapter" year="2010">CAPELLARI &amp; AMORIM 2010</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 19). Legs: mostly yellow, middle coxa (sometimes also hind coxa) and apices of tarsi brown; pulvilli small; tarsal claws present. Abdomen: usually greenish, with coppery reflections dorsally and lateral yellow spots, sometimes from tergite 1 to 6; tergite 6 with setae and bristles restricted to posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="2599EBF1DE47FFBAFCA9F84EFCF1F830" box="[801,884,1993,2017]" captionStart="Figs 1–3" captionStartId="2.[831,871,830,852]" captionTargetBox="[846,1426,226,812]" captionTargetId="figure-742@2.[831,1436,219,824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–3: Setation pattern on male tergite 6 of Chrysotus (left lateral): 1. C. neglectus (WIEDEMANN). – 2. C. spectabilis (LOEW). – 3. C. maculatus (PARENT). – Scale bar: 0.2 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1-3</figureCitation>
). Hypopygium: partially hidden under tergite 6, surstyli as a single lobe, with short spine at apex (see 
<bibRefCitation id="D9338A85DE47FFBAFC92F78EFBCDF7F0" author="CAPELLARI, R. S. &amp; AMORIM, D. S." box="[794,1096,2057,2081]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="49 - 65" refId="ref5599" refString="CAPELLARI, R. S. &amp; AMORIM, D. S. 2010: Re-description and new combination of five New World species of Chrysotus MEIGEN, with comments on the Neotropical genus Lyroneurus LOEW (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). - Zootaxa 2520: 49 - 65, 25 figs." type="book chapter" year="2010">CAPELLARI &amp; AMORIM 2010</bibRefCitation>
: figs 5 and 6).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F5B8A4FFDE44FFB9FF35FF6EFDA3FDB0" pageId="2" pageNumber="377" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BD1DF774DE44FFB9FF35FF6EFDA3FDB0" blockId="2.[189,794,233,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">
<emphasis id="8FD62B66DE44FFB9FF35FF6EFE9BFED0" bold="true" box="[189,286,233,257]" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Remarks</emphasis>
: This group includes the following three species, dealt with below, as well as 
<taxonomicName id="7AA28CF7DE44FFB9FD92FE8EFC9CFEF0" authority="(PARENT)" baseAuthorityName="PARENT" box="[538,793,265,289]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis id="8FD62B66DE44FFB9FD92FE8EFD21FEF0" box="[538,676,265,289]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">C. maculatus</emphasis>
(PARENT)
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="7AA28CF7DE44FFB9FF54FEAEFDDEFE90" authority="ROBINSON" authorityName="ROBINSON" box="[220,603,297,321]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Diaphorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculipennis">
<emphasis id="8FD62B66DE44FFB9FF54FEAEFE64FE90" box="[220,481,297,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Diaphorus maculipennis</emphasis>
ROBINSON
</taxonomicName>
; 
<typeStatus id="621949D6DE44FFB9FDE5FEAEFD4EFE90" box="[621,715,297,321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">holotype</typeStatus>
in the Natural History Museum of London, examined) and 
<taxonomicName id="7AA28CF7DE44FFB9FF35FEEEFE1CFE50" authority="PARENT" authorityName="PARENT" box="[189,409,361,385]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singularis">
<emphasis id="8FD62B66DE44FFB9FF35FEEEFEBBFE50" box="[189,318,361,385]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">C. singularis</emphasis>
PARENT
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="621949D6DE44FFB9FE20FEEEFD8DFE50" box="[424,520,361,385]" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">holotype</typeStatus>
in the SNSD, examined). Some of the diagnostic characters listed above should be regarded as apomorphies (see Discussion), in such a way that gathering these five species in a group seems justified on a reasonable hypothesis of monophyly. The group is currently known only from South America: 
<collectingCountry id="C5B5B7E4DE44FFB9FD30FD8EFC93FDF0" box="[696,790,521,545]" name="Suriname" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Surinam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="C5B5B7E4DE44FFB9FF35FDADFF74FD90" box="[189,241,554,577]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="C5B5B7E4DE44FFB9FF74FDAEFECCFD90" box="[252,329,553,577]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Bolívia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="C5B5B7E4DE44FFB9FE0AFDAEFE45FD90" box="[386,448,553,577]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Pará, 
<collectingRegion id="7F663996DE44FFB9FD85FDAEFDD9FD90" box="[525,604,553,577]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Amapá</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="7F663996DE44FFB9FDEFFDAEFD52FD90" box="[615,727,553,577]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="7F663996DE44FFB9FD6AFDADFE8FFDB0" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="7F663996DE44FFB9FE9CFDCEFE26FDB0" box="[276,419,585,609]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="7F663996DE44FFB9FE25FDCEFD9FFDB0" box="[429,538,585,609]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
